http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/smugglers-feel-the-heat/article14013601.ece

The Nindra police in the early hours of Thursday arrested a red sanders smuggler, Mahabub Basha (45) of Karnataka, and seized as many as 20 high-grade red sanders logs and a van carrying them at Nindra Cross, 35 km from Puttur. According to Nindra Sub-Inspector Mr. Balakrishna, the van was on its way to Chennai from Tirupati.When intercepted, four of those who were travelling in the vehicle fled from the scene under the cover of darkness.However, police arrested one person and seized the vehicle with logs worth around Rs. 15 lakh. A case was registered.